ciscoSmartLicMIB.name: ciscoSmartLicMIB

revisions.description: Initial Version of Cisco Smart Licensing MIB

ciscoSmartLicMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: ask-smartlicensing@cisco.com
ciscoSmartLicMIB.description: The MIB module for managing licenses on the system. The licensing mechanism provides flexibility to enforce licensing for various features in the system. The following description introduces different concepts and terminologies necessary to understand the MIB definition and to perform license management. Product Instance: An instance of a Cisco software image that runs on a hardware platform and requires some licensing capability. Software ID tag: A string generated by the Cisco Connected Software IT team to uniquely identify a Cisco software product. Smart Account: A Smart Licensing account that is created for Cisco customers or partners to manage their Smart Licensing product instances and licenses. The account is created on the Cisco Smart Software Manager portal. An enterprise account can have several virtual accounts (a.k.a. pools) of licenses. Cisco Smart Software Manager (CSSM): The Smart Licensing back-end system, hosted on Cisco IT infrastructure, is responsible for managing all Smart Licensing services and transactions. It provides a set of APIs that the Smart Agent can communicate with and an external-facing UI for Cisco customers and partners to log into and manage their Smart Licensing account. Registration Token: A token that is generated from the Cisco Smart Software Manager. The token is used to register a product instance with the Cisco Smart Software Manager. Smart Agent: A Smart Licensing software client that runs on a product instance and communicates with the Cisco Smart Software Manager. Entitlement Tag: A unique string that identifies a feature that can be enabled on a product instance. The tags are used by both the Smart Agent and the Cisco Smart Software Manager to track entitlement requests. Transport Mode: The Smart Agent uses the Smart Call Home (SCH) service as a transport medium to communicate with the Smart Licensing back-end. Crypto (LCS) Service: In addition to HTTPS exchanged messages are further signed and verified on both sides to ensure the authenticity of all communication. The Smart Software Licensing system uses a crypto service and underlying crypto library (either CiscoSSL or PKI). The Smart Software Licensing back-end leverages the Licensing Crypto Service (LCS) service. UDI: Unique Device Identifier that uniquely identifies a device. Primarily it consists of a product ID, version ID and serial number of the Customers device. Grace Period: A product enters into a grace period when the authorization period expires. This is the result of multiple authorization attempt failures which occurring 90 days after the last successful authorization. The grace period continues until the grace period expires - 90 days after the grace period starts. Counted License: Limits the number of similar entities that can consume a license. For example, a counted license when used by a feature can limit the number of IP phones that can connect or the number of tunnels that can be created. Evaluation License: An Evaluation License grants the right to a customer to enable functionality of a product instance before registering it and without an explicit portal based license for a limited amount of time. This amount of time ranges on average between 60 to 90 days. Evaluation licenses are available for most functionality, but may be limited for a variety of reasons such as legal, royalty, regulatory, or other causes. This MIB module also defines various notifications that will be triggered to asynchronously notify the management application of any critical events.

ciscoSlaInstanceId.name: ciscoSlaInstanceId
ciscoSlaInstanceId.description: This object indicates the smart licence agent's instance number.

ciscoSlaSUDIInfo.name: ciscoSlaSUDIInfo
ciscoSlaSUDIInfo.description: This object indicates the device identifier information

ciscoSlaVersion.name: ciscoSlaVersion
ciscoSlaVersion.description: This object indicates the smart licensing version information in the below shown sample format. sample format: Cisco Smart Licensing Agent, Version 1.1.0_290

ciscoSlaEnabled.name: ciscoSlaEnabled
ciscoSlaEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the smart licensing mode is enabled. A value of 'true' indicates the mode is enabled.

ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoTable.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoTable
ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoTable.description: This table contains information about all entitlements being requested from this device

ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoEntry.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoEntry
ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoEntry.description: An entry in ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoEntry. Each entry contains information about a entitlement requested on the device. This entry gets created when a license is requested successfully. Management application can not create these entries directly

ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoIndex.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoIndex
ciscoSlaEntitlementInfoIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies an entitlement record

ciscoSlaEntitlementRequestCount.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementRequestCount
ciscoSlaEntitlementRequestCount.description: Number of count that was requested for this entitlement tag. A value of 'zero' indicates that this entitlement is not in use.

ciscoSlaEntitlementTag.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementTag
ciscoSlaEntitlementTag.description: The tag name for the entitlement in use. This is abbreviated form of the entitlement tag.

ciscoSlaEntitlementVersion.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementVersion
ciscoSlaEntitlementVersion.description: This object indicates the entitlement version.

ciscoSlaEntitlementEnforceMode.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementEnforceMode
ciscoSlaEntitlementEnforceMode.description: This object indicates the enforce mode for the entitlement tag. In Entitlement notifications this will indicate the enforcement mode of an individual entitlement. In global notifications this indicates the overall enforcement mode in the agent.

ciscoSlaEntitlementDescription.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementDescription
ciscoSlaEntitlementDescription.description: This object indicates the description for the entitlements. This value is only available after the agent receives a response from CSSM to an Authorization request. If the description is unknown this object will contain a null string.

ciscoSlaEntitlementFeatureName.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementFeatureName
ciscoSlaEntitlementFeatureName.description: This value is the short feature name for the entitlement and is only available after the agent receives a response from CSSM to an Authorization request. If its value is unknown this object will contain a null string.

ciscoSlaRegistrationStatus.name: ciscoSlaRegistrationStatus
ciscoSlaRegistrationStatus.description: Smart Agent Registration Status. This is the status of the registration initiated using the token generated from the Cisco Licensing portal.

ciscoSlaVirtualAccount.name: ciscoSlaVirtualAccount
ciscoSlaVirtualAccount.description: The virtual account name created in the Licensing Portal to which this device will be registered.

ciscoSlaNextCertificateExpireTime.name: ciscoSlaNextCertificateExpireTime
ciscoSlaNextCertificateExpireTime.description: The next expiration date/time of ID Certificate in UTC epoch seconds.

ciscoSlaEnterpriseAccountName.name: ciscoSlaEnterpriseAccountName
ciscoSlaEnterpriseAccountName.description: The enterprise account name as configured in the Cisco Licensing Portal.

ciscoSlaRegisterInitTime.name: ciscoSlaRegisterInitTime
ciscoSlaRegisterInitTime.description: Time in UTC epoch seconds when the Registration of the Smart Agent was initialized.

ciscoSlaRegisterSuccess.name: ciscoSlaRegisterSuccess
ciscoSlaRegisterSuccess.description: Status of the last attempted Registration of Smart Agent

ciscoSlaRegisterFailureReason.name: ciscoSlaRegisterFailureReason
ciscoSlaRegisterFailureReason.description: Reason for the failure of the last Registration Attempt

ciscoSlaRegisterNextRetryTime.name: ciscoSlaRegisterNextRetryTime
ciscoSlaRegisterNextRetryTime.description: Time in UTC epoch seconds when the next registration attempt will be made.

ciscoSlaRenewInitTime.name: ciscoSlaRenewInitTime
ciscoSlaRenewInitTime.description: Time in UTC epoch seconds when the ID Cert renewal was initialized

ciscoSlaRenewSuccess.name: ciscoSlaRenewSuccess
ciscoSlaRenewSuccess.description: Status of Renewal of ID Certificate

ciscoSlaRenewFailureReason.name: ciscoSlaRenewFailureReason
ciscoSlaRenewFailureReason.description: Reason for the failure of the last attempted ID Cert Renewal

ciscoSlaRenewNextRetryTime.name: ciscoSlaRenewNextRetryTime
ciscoSlaRenewNextRetryTime.description: Time in UTC epoch seconds when the next ID Cert renewal will be tried.

ciscoSlaAuthExpireTime.name: ciscoSlaAuthExpireTime
ciscoSlaAuthExpireTime.description: The time in UTC epoch seconds when the authorization will expire if not renewed

ciscoSlaAuthComplianceStatus.name: ciscoSlaAuthComplianceStatus
ciscoSlaAuthComplianceStatus.description: Overall enforcement status of Smart Licensing in the device.

ciscoSlaAuthOOCStartTime.name: ciscoSlaAuthOOCStartTime
ciscoSlaAuthOOCStartTime.description: The time in UTC epoch seconds Smart Agent entered Out of Compliance state for this device.

ciscoSlaAuthEvalPeriodInUse.name: ciscoSlaAuthEvalPeriodInUse
ciscoSlaAuthEvalPeriodInUse.description: Indicates if the Evaluation Period is in Use or not

ciscoSlaAuthEvalExpiredTime.name: ciscoSlaAuthEvalExpiredTime
ciscoSlaAuthEvalExpiredTime.description: Time in UTC epoch seconds when the Evaluation Period had expired.

ciscoSlaAuthEvalPeriodLeft.name: ciscoSlaAuthEvalPeriodLeft
ciscoSlaAuthEvalPeriodLeft.description: Amount of Time left in the Evaluation Period

ciscoSlaAuthRenewInitTime.name: ciscoSlaAuthRenewInitTime
ciscoSlaAuthRenewInitTime.description: Smart Agent Authorization Renewal Initialization Time in UTC epoch seconds

ciscoSlaAuthRenewSuccess.name: ciscoSlaAuthRenewSuccess
ciscoSlaAuthRenewSuccess.description: This object indicates the authorization renewal status. A value of 'true' indicates the renewal was successful.

ciscoSlaAuthRenewFailureReason.name: ciscoSlaAuthRenewFailureReason
ciscoSlaAuthRenewFailureReason.description: This object indicates the reason for the failure of the last renewal request.

ciscoSlaAuthRenewNextRetryTime.name: ciscoSlaAuthRenewNextRetryTime
ciscoSlaAuthRenewNextRetryTime.description: Time in UTC epoch seconds when the next renewal will be retried.

ciscoSlaGlobalNotifEnable.name: ciscoSlaGlobalNotifEnable
ciscoSlaGlobalNotifEnable.description: This object indicates whether the device should generate the global notifications related to Smart Agent. This object enables/disables sending following notifications: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnforcementMode, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyReady, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnabled, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyDisabled, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterFailed, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterSuccess, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpired, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewSuccess, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewFail, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewSuccess, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewFail, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationFailure, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationRestored, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewNotStarted, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertOutOfRange, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifySystemClockChanged, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpiryWarning, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpired, ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpiryWarning

ciscoSlaEntitlementNotifEnable.name: ciscoSlaEntitlementNotifEnable
ciscoSlaEntitlementNotifEnable.description: This object indicates whether the device should generate the notifications related to entitlement enforce mode in Smart Agent. This object enables/disables sending following notifications: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEntitlementEnforceMode

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnforcementMode.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnforcementMode
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnforcementMode.description: The device generates this notification when the overall enforcement mode in the agent changes.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyReady.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyReady
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyReady.description: The device generates this notification when the Smart agent is initialized and ready.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnabled.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnabled
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEnabled.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing has been enabled.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyDisabled.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyDisabled
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyDisabled.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing has been disabled

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterFailed.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterFailed
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterFailed.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing registration with Cisco Software Manager has failed

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterSuccess.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterSuccess
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyRegisterSuccess.description: The device generates this notification when smart licensing registration with Cisco Software Manager has succeeded.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpired.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpired
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpired.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing ID (node) certificate has expired

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewSucce.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewSuccess
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewSucce.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing ID (node) certificate renewal has succeded.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewFail.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewFail
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewFail.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing ID (node) certificate renewal has failed.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewSuccess.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewSuccess
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewSuccess.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing entitlement (AUTH) renew was successful.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewFail.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewFail
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyAuthRenewFail.description: The device generates this notification when Smart licensing entitlement (AUTH) renew has failed

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationFai.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationFailure
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationFai.description: The device generates this notification when Smart Agent failed to communicate with CSSM.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationRes.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationRestored
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyCommunicationRes.description: The device generates this notification when Smart Agent communication with CSSM has been restored

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewNotSt.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewNotStarted
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertRenewNotSt.description: The device generates this notification when Smart Agent Id (Node) certificate renewal is not started

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEntitlementEnfor.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEntitlementEnforceMode
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEntitlementEnfor.description: The device generates this notification when the enforcement mode of an entitlement has changed.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertOutOfRange.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertOutOfRange
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertOutOfRange.description: The device generates this notification when the ID certificate is out of the valid range after the system clock changed. It means the current time is either before the start time or after the end time of the certificate.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifySystemClockChang.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifySystemClockChanged
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifySystemClockChang.description: The device generates this notification when the system clock has changed.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpiryWarnin.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpiryWarning
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpiryWarnin.description: The device generates this notification to warn regarding the impending evaluation time expiry.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpired.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpired
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyEvalExpired.description: The device generates this notification to notify the expiration of the evaluation period.

ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpiryWarn.name: ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpiryWarning
ciscoSlaSmartAgentNotifyIdCertExpiryWarn.description: The device generates this notification to warn regarding the impending expiry of the id (node) certificate.

ciscoSlaMIBCompliance.name: ciscoSlaMIBCompliance
ciscoSlaMIBCompliance.description: Compliance statement for Cisco Smart license MIB.

ciscoSlaMIBEntitlementInfoGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBEntitlementInfoGroup
ciscoSlaMIBEntitlementInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects for Entitlements requested and their related information.

ciscoSlaMIBRegistrationStatusInfoGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBRegistrationStatusInfoGroup
ciscoSlaMIBRegistrationStatusInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects representing the information regarding the registration status of the device.

ciscoSlaMIBGlobalNotificationGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBGlobalNotificationGroup
ciscoSlaMIBGlobalNotificationGroup.description: A collection of global notifications related to Smart Agent

ciscoSlaMIBAgentInfoGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBAgentInfoGroup
ciscoSlaMIBAgentInfoGroup.description: A collection of objects representing meta data related to Smart Agent state

ciscoSlaMIBEntitlementNotifGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBEntitlementNotifGroup
ciscoSlaMIBEntitlementNotifGroup.description: A collection of notifications related to entitlement enforce mode in SmartAgent

ciscoSlaMIBNotificationEnableGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBNotificationEnableGroup
ciscoSlaMIBNotificationEnableGroup.description: A collection of objects for controlling (enabling/disabling) license notifications to a management application.

ciscoSlaMIBAuthorizationInfoGroup.name: ciscoSlaMIBAuthorizationInfoGroup
ciscoSlaMIBAuthorizationInfoGroup.description: A collection of MIB objects representing the Authorization State of the Smart Agent.
